parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty wiring harness can cause the vehicle to malfunction, resulting in a loss of acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle does not accelerate when pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle goes into open throttle position unexpectedly

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Engine Compartment Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a sudden and unexpected engine compartment fire, which can lead to serious injury or death, as well as significant damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: No warning lights or indications of a problem

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Short Circuit Causing Battery Drain
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system short circuit can cause the battery to drain, leading to difficulty or inability to start the vehicle, which can leave the driver stranded and potentially cause accidents.
The disintegration of the wire plastic insulation around the engine can cause electrical shorts, leading to engine stalling, reduced engine performance, and potentially, engine fires.
symptoms: Wire insulation around the engine is crumbling or disintegrating

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially when driving at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Brake lights do not turn on
brake lights remain on even when the brake pedal is not pressed
